Arrangement.text: It is good to give thanks to the LORD, to sing praises to your name, O Most High; To declare your steadfast love in the morning, and your faithfulness by night, To the music of the lute and the harp, to the melody of the lyre. For you, O LORD, have made me glad by your work; at the works of your hands I sing for joy.
